The '''Papuan grassbird''' ('''''Cincloramphus macrurus''''') is a species of [[Megalurus|typical grassbird]] in the family [[Locustellidae]]. The species was once treated as several subspecies of the [[tawny grassbird]], but the two do not interbreed where their ranges are sympatric. The species is [[endemism|endemic]] to [[New Guinea]] and its satellite islands. There are seven subspecies ranging across montane areas of New Guinea, [[New Britain]] and [[New Ireland (island)|New Ireland]]. It is a fairly large typical grassbird, {{convert|20|-|23|cm|in|abbr=on}} long and weighing {{convert|40|g|oz|abbr=on}}.

